title: The Outer Banks, North Carolina
description: A comprehensive study of The Outer Banks, exploring its geography, history, culture, and economy. This course delves deep into various aspects of The Outer Banks, showcasing its importance and impact.
learningObjectives: Understand the geography and landscape of The Outer Banks
Learn the history and culture of The Outer Banks
Analyze the economy of The Outer Banks
Understand the ecological importance of The Outer Banks

finalProjectDetails.overview: A comprehensive project combining all learning objectives including creating a detailed report on The Outer Banks.
finalProjectDetails.submissionInstructions: The final project should be submitted in a PDF format, not exceeding 20 pages including references. It should be emailed to the instructor by the last day of the course.
